WEBVTT

00:00:05.110 --> 00:00:07.730
To understand the discount of cash

00:00:07.730 --> 00:00:09.790
flows, or discount of cash

00:00:09.790 --> 00:00:11.910
flows, I want to go

00:00:11.910 --> 00:00:14.890
deeper into the concept of

00:00:14.890 --> 00:00:16.490
discounting or updating,

00:00:16.490 --> 00:00:19.890
which we saw in previous classes.

00:00:20.330 --> 00:00:22.050
Well, discounting or updating is calculating

00:00:22.050 --> 00:00:24.670
the value today, the present value,

00:00:24.670 --> 00:00:27.890
the current value of a cash

00:00:27.890 --> 00:00:29.690
flow, of a charge, of a payment

00:00:29.690 --> 00:00:34.610
that occurs in the periods.

00:00:34.670 --> 00:00:37.230
And what we do is bring it to the present

00:00:37.230 --> 00:00:38.930
moment to see how much it is worth

00:00:38.930 --> 00:00:39.570
today.

00:00:40.450 --> 00:00:41.930
As we have seen, we have

00:00:41.930 --> 00:00:43.230
to consider the value of

00:00:43.230 --> 00:00:44.150
money in time.

00:00:45.090 --> 00:00:46.710
One million euros in five years.

00:00:46.850 --> 00:00:47.890
How much is it worth today?

00:00:47.990 --> 00:00:49.470
We are trying to discount

00:00:49.470 --> 00:00:50.370
that million.

00:00:50.890 --> 00:00:51.810
And how do we do it?

00:00:52.150 --> 00:00:53.650
The formula is this.

00:00:53.970 --> 00:00:55.430
The present value or current

00:00:55.430 --> 00:00:58.030
value is equal to that cash flow

00:00:58.030 --> 00:01:01.390
divided to bring it, to discount

00:01:01.390 --> 00:01:02.910
it, to update it, we divide it between

00:01:02.910 --> 00:01:06.150
an upgrade or discount factor,

00:01:06.150 --> 00:01:07.630
which is equal to one plus

00:01:07.630 --> 00:01:09.850
the interest rate raised

00:01:09.850 --> 00:01:13.130
to n, which is the number

00:01:13.130 --> 00:01:14.250
of periods.

00:01:14.450 --> 00:01:15.710
By the way, here I want you to keep

00:01:15.710 --> 00:01:17.250
in mind that here we’ve

00:01:17.250 --> 00:01:19.070
talked about interest rate I,

00:01:19.510 --> 00:01:21.030
but really this is the upgrade

00:01:21.030 --> 00:01:22.990
rate or it’s the discount rate.

00:01:23.370 --> 00:01:25.110
And sometimes you’ll see it written,

00:01:25.610 --> 00:01:27.910
for example, with the letter K, or with the

00:01:27.910 --> 00:01:28.670
letter D.

00:01:28.690 --> 00:01:30.550
Well, it depends on the context in which

00:01:30.550 --> 00:01:32.510
it is used, but I want you to understand it.

00:01:32.750 --> 00:01:34.290
It is the upgrade rate, it is the

00:01:34.290 --> 00:01:37.610
discount rate we will use to

00:01:37.610 --> 00:01:40.150
divide that future cash flow and

00:01:40.150 --> 00:01:42.190
bring it to the current moment.

00:01:44.090 --> 00:01:45.310
Well, let’s see an example.

00:01:46.790 --> 00:01:48.270
We will think that in this case the

00:01:48.270 --> 00:01:50.510
discount rate or interest rate

00:01:50.510 --> 00:01:53.290
is 10% and that we want to discount

00:01:53.290 --> 00:01:56.290
200,000 euros that we will charge,

00:01:56.290 --> 00:01:57.530
for example, in this case it

00:01:57.530 --> 00:01:59.050
is a charge within three years

00:01:59.050 --> 00:02:00.590
and we bring it at the current time.

00:02:00.590 --> 00:02:02.450
We use the formula.

00:02:02.550 --> 00:02:07.150
We have 200,000 between 1 plus

00:02:07.150 --> 00:02:08.710
10% elevated to 3.

00:02:09.030 --> 00:02:10.430
Well, in the end we are dividing 200,

00:02:10.430 --> 00:02:12.030
000 between 1 by 33.

00:02:13.730 --> 00:02:15.930
And from this formula what we get is

00:02:15.930 --> 00:02:17.990
that the current value or present

00:02:17.990 --> 00:02:19.890
value of those 200,000 euros

00:02:19.890 --> 00:02:23.030
when we bring them to date is equal

00:02:23.030 --> 00:02:26.130
to 150.263.

00:02:27.190 --> 00:02:28.430
So, what does this depend on?

00:02:28.490 --> 00:02:31.150
What is the current value of

00:02:31.150 --> 00:02:32.190
a future cash flow?

00:02:32.190 --> 00:02:33.770
It depends on, as we are seeing in

00:02:33.770 --> 00:02:35.610
the formula, the variables are the

00:02:35.610 --> 00:02:38.170
discount rate and the number of periods.

00:02:38.330 --> 00:02:39.250
What happens if, for example,

00:02:39.470 --> 00:02:40.850
we increase the discount rate

00:02:40.850 --> 00:02:43.970
and we double the discount rate?

00:02:44.310 --> 00:02:45.730
This is a $20,000 discount, but in this

00:02:45.730 --> 00:02:48.450
case we will be discounted at 20% instead

00:02:48.450 --> 00:02:50.370
of 10%.

00:02:50.370 --> 00:02:51.950
Well, as you can see, it is very clear

00:02:51.950 --> 00:02:53.770
in the formula because it is in the

00:02:53.770 --> 00:02:54.430
denominator.

00:02:54.490 --> 00:02:56.290
We are dividing by a larger

00:02:56.290 --> 00:02:57.190
amount.

00:02:57.850 --> 00:02:59.230
So in this case the current

00:02:59.230 --> 00:03:01.870
value, which was 150,000 euros

00:03:01.870 --> 00:03:06.410
before, in this case are 115,741.

00:03:07.190 --> 00:03:08.910
If we increase the discount

00:03:08.910 --> 00:03:10.270
rate, if we discount at a higher

00:03:10.270 --> 00:03:13.050
rate, the current value is lower.

00:03:13.570 --> 00:03:14.730
It is quite logical.

00:03:15.150 --> 00:03:16.530
You probably already know what

00:03:16.530 --> 00:03:18.710
it means to update or discount.

00:03:19.050 --> 00:03:20.470
We have seen the example with

00:03:20.470 --> 00:03:21.430
a single amount.

00:03:22.210 --> 00:03:23.650
We calculated what the current

00:03:23.650 --> 00:03:26.090
value of 200,000 euros we will receive

00:03:26.090 --> 00:03:28.170
within three years and we discounted

00:03:28.170 --> 00:03:30.790
them with two discount rates,

00:03:30.790 --> 00:03:32.550
which were with 10 and

00:03:32.550 --> 00:03:34.890
20%.

00:03:34.890 --> 00:03:36.330
Well, the discount of cash

00:03:36.330 --> 00:03:38.050
flows is ultimately the same.

00:03:38.310 --> 00:03:39.530
What happens is that in this case

00:03:39.530 --> 00:03:40.810
we will apply it to a series

00:03:40.810 --> 00:03:42.710
of cash flows or a series of cash

00:03:42.710 --> 00:03:44.470
flows, but we will do the same.

00:03:44.530 --> 00:03:46.750
We will bring them all to the current

00:03:46.750 --> 00:03:48.430
moment and we will calculate the current

00:03:48.430 --> 00:03:50.270
value or present value of that flow

00:03:50.270 --> 00:03:57.370
of Today we make an investment of

