00:04:07.370 --> 00:04:08.230
But look, we could put

00:04:08.230 --> 00:04:10.590
different amounts.

00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:11.890
We will be counting the

00:04:11.890 --> 00:04:12.450
cash flow.

00:04:12.530 --> 00:04:15.050
Let’s calculate how much all those

00:04:15.050 --> 00:04:16.650
future cash flows are worth today,

00:04:16.750 --> 00:04:18.470
taking into account the value

00:04:18.470 --> 00:04:19.310
of money over time.

00:04:20.350 --> 00:04:21.090
And how do we do it?

00:04:21.630 --> 00:04:24.750
What we’re going to do is calculate

00:04:24.750 --> 00:04:25.430
the cash flow and bring it

00:04:25.430 --> 00:04:26.650
to the current moment.

00:04:27.070 --> 00:04:28.870
We will bring the 200,000 euros of the

00:04:28.870 --> 00:04:31.530
year 4, we will discount them and we will

00:04:31.530 --> 00:04:33.310
calculate how much they are worth today.

00:04:33.610 --> 00:04:36.950
And we will add the current value

00:04:36.950 --> 00:04:39.110
of the 200,000 euros we will receive

00:04:39.110 --> 00:04:40.390
within three years, two years,

00:04:40.390 --> 00:04:42.270
a year, etc.

00:04:42.330 --> 00:04:44.310
We will add it all and we will

00:04:44.310 --> 00:04:45.670
calculate what the current value

00:04:45.670 --> 00:04:46.810
of all those future cash

00:04:46.810 --> 00:04:47.910
flows will be.

00:04:49.430 --> 00:04:50.450
What is the formula for this?

00:04:50.510 --> 00:04:51.290
very simple though.

00:04:51.370 --> 00:04:54.610
It is the same as the one

00:04:54.610 --> 00:04:56.530
we have studied the discount, the update.

00:04:56.890 --> 00:04:58.150
What happens is that in this case

00:04:58.150 --> 00:04:59.870
we will add the different cash

00:04:59.870 --> 00:05:01.510
flows so easily.

